      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) must agree with experimental measurements within combined simulation and experimental uncertainty bands across all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "NIH predictions at all five flow-speed operating points fall within the combined uncertainty band (simulation GCI + experimental measurement uncertainty). Maximum normalized error is 8.1% at the highest flow condition. Achieved level meets required level."
