      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QoI (absolute NIH) must be directly linked to the clinical decision threshold; indirect surrogates are not acceptable at MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the absolute normalized index of hemolysis, which maps directly to the clinical acceptance threshold of NIH < 0.01 g/100 L. No surrogate quantities are used. Achieved level meets required level."
