      "acceptanceCriteria": "All uncertain model inputs must be characterized by probability distributions and propagated through the model via Monte Carlo UQ with at least 500 samples.",
      "rationale": "Six uncertain inputs (viscosity, hematocrit, power-law exponents alpha and beta, inlet velocity profile, wall roughness) are characterized by normal or uniform distributions derived from experimental data. Monte Carlo UQ with 1000 samples performed. 95th-percentile NIH remains below clinical threshold. Achieved level meets required level."
